track_notes:
This trip is as rewarding as it is long and exhausting. This was my way up. It starts at some free parking spots that I discovered by chance. I rode my bicycle to Gotzenalm, which took me around 2 hours - no electricity involved. The last ascent was very steep such that I had to push my bike, but it was still worth it for the fast and fun way down. From Gotzenalm it took me half an hour of walking to Regenalm and yet another half an hour navigating through a maze of fallen trees on the final ascent up to the summit. In total my way up was exactly 3 hours long. Counter ascents must not be underestimated on this route.

Thanks to Andreas DK7MG for sharing the experience from his first activation with me. He took a boat to the south end of KÃ¶nigssee from where he started his hike. I have seen some warning signs, that a landslide has significantly increased the difficulty and danger on this way up. Additionally I did not want to depend on the boat times.
